# Force LF line endings on text files that are interpreted by Linux
# in production. Without this, a Windows checkout (with the default
# core.autocrlf=true) ships CRLF endings, which can break shell-script
# parsing on a remote Linux box (a 2-minute outage on a sister repo,
# meta-council, was caused by exactly this in 2026-04-27).

*.sh        text eol=lf
*.py        text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.toml      text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
Makefile    text eol=lf
